        dc:description           "Figs. 2-10. Sphedanolestes rubripes, new species. 2, head and pronotum, antenna partly removed; 3, apical portion of right fore leg; 4. apical portion of left hind leg; 5, abdomen of female; 6, 7, abdominal apex of female; 8, pygophore; 9, apical portion of pygophore, showing pygophore process and claspers; 10, clasper; 2-5,10, lateral view; 6, 8, 9, ventral view; 7, caudal view. Scale: for Figs. 2, 5-8, 1 mm; for Figs. 3, 4, 9, 10, 0.5 mm." ;
